Marill

Evolves At 4

Huge Power

Passive Ability

When this Pokémon hits only a single enemy with an auto attack, a move, or their Unite Move, the hit is always a critical hit. However, when hitting two or more enemies at once with an auto attack, a move, or its Unite Move, the hits are never critical hits.

Critical hits deal 170% rather than 200%.

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, dealing increased damage to enemies within a cone area of effect in front of this Pokémon.

Tackle

Move 1

5.00s Dash

Charge forward; dealing damage to any enemy hit and leave them unable to act for 0.5s.

86% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 100

Tackle Upgrade Choices

Play Rough

5.00s Buff

Increase movement speed by 30% for 4s and change the next auto attack. When performing the next auto attack, lunge at one enemy in range and deliver repeated blows dealing damage to that target and leave it unable to act for .75s.

Using Play Rough will overwrite any active Aqua Tail attack change. Play Rough attacks count as auto attacks for the purpose of items, lifesteal and other benefits.

39% Atk + 4 x (Level - 1) + 60

Further increases movement speed to 35% when this move is used, and also reduces this move’s cooldown by 1s.

Water Pulse

5.00s Ranged

Shoot a pulsing blast of water in front of Azumarill. When shooting the blast, Azumarill may perform a short rolling dash in a designated direction. When the blast of water hits an enemy, decrease their movement speed by 40% for 2s and deal damage to all enemies in an area of effect around the initial target. The blast of water then automatically bounces to another target if one is available. Including the first target, the blast of water can bounce between up to three targets consecutively, and each hit behaves in the same way as the first.

87% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 120

Increase the maximum number of targets that the blast of water can bounce between by 2.

Bubble

Move 2

6.00s Area

Spray bubbles in a cone dealing damage to enemies in the area of effect and decreasing their movement speed by 30% for 2s. This move can be used while moving.

74% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 80

Bubble Upgrade Choices

Whirlpool

9.00s Area

For 5s, four small whirlpools appear that swirl around Azumarill as it moves. If a whirlpool hits a wild Pokémon, the whirlpool deals damage to them and restores Azumarill's HP. If a whirlpool hits an enemy player, an increased amount of HP is restored.

Moving clockwise against your target will grant more hits against that target, and counter-clockwise will reduce the number of hits.

34% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 60

6% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 10

18% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 30

Reduces this move’s cooldown by 2s and increases the amount of HP restored.

8% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 15

24% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 45

Aqua Tail

7.00s Buff

Increase area-of-effect and attack speed for the next three auto attacks by 20% for 6s. If these auto attacks hit from a distance, they also deal increased damage and restore HP. Using Aqua Tail will overwrite any active Play Rough attack change.

Aqua Tail attacks count as auto attacks for the purpose of items, lifesteal and other benefits.

68% Atk + 2 x (Level - 1) + 50

122.4% Atk + 3 x (Level - 1) + 90

136% Atk + 4 x (Level - 1) + 100

244.8% Atk + 6 x (Level - 1) + 180

110% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 220

Aqua Tail attacks that hit from a distance reduce the cooldown of all moves by 0.8s.

Belly Bash

Unite Move

89s 80000 Sure Hit

Unlocks at level 8

Azumarill targets an enemy player and then pounds their belly three times; losing 5% remaining HP with each pound in exchange for a 6.5% max HP shield that stacks with each pound and lasts 6s. Azumarill gains 60 Attack for 5s and can move while pounding their belly. Azumarill then charges at the target damaging and throwing all Pokémon hit while charging and Pokémon within the area effect around the target. Azumarill is unstoppable during this move.

108% Atk + 9 x (Level - 1) + 260

0% Atk + 5 x (Level - 1) + 60

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 30% CDR, 20% Max HP Shield
